'''World Perfume''' is a [[perfume]] company based in [[Dallas]], [[Texas]]. The president of the company, Johnny Whitworth, was once a distributor for [[Scentura]].<ref name = "rich"> {{cite journal | first =E. | last =Thomas Jr. | authorlink = | coauthors = |date=October 5, 1987 | title =Who Wants To Be Rich? Larry Hahn: From Sleeping In A Car To A $5 Million Home | journal =Atlanta Business Chronicle | volume =10 | issue =19 | pages =1 (5) | id = | url = }} </ref><ref name="WP2">{{cite web|title=World Perfume |work=worldperfumeinc |url=http://www.worldperfumeinc.com/staff.asp |accessdate=2006-01-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070403033612/http://www.worldperfumeinc.com/staff.asp |archivedate=April 3, 2007 }} </ref> World Perfume distributors buy perfume from headquarters and recruit salesmen with newspaper ads. Door-to-door salespeople are paid based on their sales commission, with no salary.<ref name = "first"> {{cite journal | first =Ron | last =Reagan | authorlink = | coauthors = |date=November 2, 2001 | title =Scents Of Deception: To Buy Or Not To Buy | journal =News 5, Cleveland Ohio | volume = | issue = | pages = | id = | url =http://www.newsnet5.com/specialassignment/1040015/detail.html }} </ref>
Like Scentura, media publicity of the company has been negative.<ref name = "first"/>
The company was opened in 1989.<ref name="WP">{{cite web|title=World Perfume |work=worldperfumeinc |url=http://www.worldperfumeinc.com/ |accessdate=2006-01-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070403033639/http://www.worldperfumeinc.com/ |archivedate=April 3, 2007 }} </ref> It closed in 2007.{{fact|date=November 2011}}
